01:54.170 --> 02:00.170
♪

02:09.185 --> 02:11.485
♪

02:11.486 --> 02:12.687
(LIGHTER CLICKING)

02:12.688 --> 02:18.688
♪

02:24.132 --> 02:27.300
_

02:27.429 --> 02:29.835
_

02:30.371 --> 02:35.841
♪

02:35.843 --> 02:37.376
We'll hole up here.

02:37.377 --> 02:38.679
SASHA: The smell.

02:38.680 --> 02:40.080
It's like leather soup.

02:41.516 --> 02:43.349
This is what it's come to.

02:43.351 --> 02:45.184
It worked well enough for the
Spanish, it'll work for us.

02:45.186 --> 02:48.421
- We regroup, get our numbers up.
- Whoa...

02:48.423 --> 02:50.689
Check this out.

02:50.691 --> 02:56.691
♪

03:04.705 --> 03:07.505
We're the outlaws now.

03:07.507 --> 03:10.342
ELENA'S VOICE: <i>It's time
to embrace our fate.</i>

03:10.344 --> 03:13.712
<i>This won't stop until it happens.</i>

03:13.714 --> 03:15.547
<i>So let it come.</i>

03:15.549 --> 03:21.549
♪

03:30.563 --> 03:36.563
♪

03:47.595 --> 03:50.618
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

03:51.595 --> 03:54.162
♪

03:55.313 --> 03:57.313
My friend,

03:57.315 --> 03:59.648
all of our money is in this room.

03:59.650 --> 04:01.117
It's in the dumbwaiter.

04:01.119 --> 04:03.086
If you set us free you
could have it all.

04:08.326 --> 04:11.460
_

04:13.664 --> 04:15.664
He doesn't speak English.

04:15.666 --> 04:18.401
Great, so we can talk. What's the plan?

04:18.403 --> 04:20.668
(DOOR OPENS; FOOTSTEPS)

04:20.671 --> 04:23.338
The plan was never to
be in your own cage.

04:23.340 --> 04:24.973
That much is obvious.

04:24.975 --> 04:27.376
You would have given
yourselves a toilet.

04:28.678 --> 04:31.846
No, just a grate in the floor.

04:31.848 --> 04:34.516
I'm guessing mostly
blood goes down there.

04:34.518 --> 04:37.519
- Yours will be next.
- There is too much death,

04:37.521 --> 04:39.521
too much bloodshed.

04:39.523 --> 04:42.690
In order to eliminate war between Packs,

04:42.692 --> 04:45.527
I will eliminate Packs.

04:45.529 --> 04:48.362
All of us, under one Alpha.

04:48.364 --> 04:49.831
You?

04:49.833 --> 04:51.533
Yeah.

04:51.535 --> 04:53.367
The other Alphas will resist this.

04:53.369 --> 04:55.369
The numbers are in my favour.

04:55.371 --> 04:57.371
I will roll across all territories,

04:57.373 --> 05:00.374
and they will bow

05:00.376 --> 05:02.376
or die.

05:02.378 --> 05:04.711
Tell me, in a room with so much lore,

05:04.713 --> 05:07.848
are there tales of being hunted?

05:08.717 --> 05:11.218
Every Pack has been hunted,

05:11.220 --> 05:12.719
in one way or another.

05:12.721 --> 05:15.556
During Soviet era, there
was a bounty on wolves.

05:15.558 --> 05:18.024
1.5 million were killed,

05:18.026 --> 05:21.695
hunters were paid the equivalent of $75.

05:22.898 --> 05:26.700
$75, that is how much we were worth.

05:27.903 --> 05:31.504
But you, Danvers, are priceless.

05:31.506 --> 05:33.506
And why is that?

05:33.508 --> 05:37.243
In Russia, we have a
tradition called Okhota,

05:37.245 --> 05:39.045
"the Hunt".

05:39.047 --> 05:42.782
The new Alpha allows his
Pack to hunt the old.

05:42.784 --> 05:44.917
As a gift.

05:44.919 --> 05:47.420
You think I'm going to let
you force me to Change,

05:47.422 --> 05:49.589
as a gift?

05:49.591 --> 05:52.424
Tomorrow at noon my Pack will hunt you.

05:52.426 --> 05:54.426
If you refuse, we will kill Nick.

05:54.428 --> 05:57.563
(SCOFFING) They'll kill me anyway.

05:58.600 --> 06:01.333
Enjoy the cold comfort of your cage.

06:01.335 --> 06:07.335
♪

06:08.976 --> 06:11.176
_

06:11.178 --> 06:13.145
CLAY: I'm going to argue with
you about this, darlin'.

06:13.147 --> 06:15.614
I am going, and you're going to stay.

06:18.352 --> 06:21.786
I'm not going to let you come
with me, not in your condition.

06:21.788 --> 06:23.788
You can't go back there alone.

06:23.790 --> 06:26.257
They have Jeremy and Nick.

06:26.259 --> 06:28.793
He won't have killed Jeremy, not yet.

06:28.795 --> 06:31.963
Konstantin will take
advantage of his position.

06:31.965 --> 06:34.966
There is a Russian tradition
to hunt the defeated Alpha.

06:34.968 --> 06:37.635
And they will not miss
the chance to do so.

06:37.637 --> 06:39.270
Jeremy's no longer Alpha.

06:39.272 --> 06:41.139
But if Konstantin doesn't know that,

06:41.141 --> 06:42.973
there's no way Jeremy will give that up.

06:42.975 --> 06:44.808
What about Nick? What happens with him?

06:44.810 --> 06:47.978
There is no provision for the second.

06:47.980 --> 06:49.813
Okay, we treat this
like a rescue mission,

06:49.815 --> 06:51.449
until we know what we're dealing with.

06:51.451 --> 06:53.617
Tradition marks the beginning
of the Hunt at midday.

06:53.619 --> 06:55.986
If they're all out there,
then the house is empty.

06:55.988 --> 06:57.988
We get there, you go in and find Nick.

06:57.990 --> 07:00.323
The rest of us, we go after Jeremy.

07:00.325 --> 07:02.826
The rest of us?

07:02.828 --> 07:04.494
Against how many of them?

07:04.496 --> 07:06.030
We call Marsten.

07:06.031 --> 07:07.331
Cain. Anson.

07:07.332 --> 07:09.499
Call them all.

07:09.500 --> 07:10.701
Got it?

07:10.702 --> 07:12.102
(PHONE RINGING)

07:16.475 --> 07:17.875
Gentlemen.

07:17.876 --> 07:20.210
Gentlemen, please.

07:20.212 --> 07:22.645
A moment, oof! Heh!

07:25.517 --> 07:27.349
There are but two ways

07:27.351 --> 07:29.518
to judge a man at first sight.

07:29.520 --> 07:31.520
His shoes, and his watch.

07:31.522 --> 07:34.691
Not the calibre or the quality,

07:34.693 --> 07:36.492
but the care.

07:36.494 --> 07:39.862
See, a poor man can still buff
his shoes to a smart shine.

07:39.864 --> 07:42.331
He can still polish his watch.

07:42.333 --> 07:45.834
These things say... I respect myself.

07:47.871 --> 07:50.372
There is but one way, ultimately,

07:50.374 --> 07:52.874
to judge a werewolf,

07:52.876 --> 07:56.345
the grace with which he dies.

07:56.347 --> 07:58.714
We will let you live if
you pledge allegiance

07:58.716 --> 08:01.249
to Konstantin Saranin.

08:01.251 --> 08:03.384
Absurd.

08:03.386 --> 08:06.688
I serve Elena Michaels.

08:07.557 --> 08:09.725
- (GRUNTING)
- Argh!

08:09.727 --> 08:13.361
(MOANING, PANTING)

08:16.566 --> 08:18.733
(GRUNT)

08:18.735 --> 08:21.102
(CHUCKLING)

08:21.103 --> 08:22.304
(KNIFE SLICING)

08:22.305 --> 08:25.406
♪

08:25.408 --> 08:27.275
- (GUNSHOT)
- Argh!

08:27.277 --> 08:29.310
(MOANING)

08:29.312 --> 08:32.980
(PANTING, GROANING)

08:32.982 --> 08:36.717
♪

08:36.719 --> 08:41.421
You pledge your allegiance to
Konstantin Saranin as your Alpha.

08:41.423 --> 08:44.424
My Alpha is Elena Michaels.

08:44.426 --> 08:50.426
♪

08:59.441 --> 09:05.441
♪

09:06.581 --> 09:10.616
We won't stop chasing you until you
take Konstantin Saranin as your Alpha!

09:10.618 --> 09:13.920
Suck it, bro! I follow Elena Michaels!

09:16.124 --> 09:18.624
There has been an
interesting development.

09:18.626 --> 09:20.960
My Pack has been tracking yours.

09:20.962 --> 09:22.428
Offering them a chance to live,

09:22.430 --> 09:24.630
if they accept me as their new Alpha.

09:24.632 --> 09:27.333
And they won't accept you.

09:27.335 --> 09:28.735
You are right.

09:30.638 --> 09:32.971
Because, according to them,

09:32.973 --> 09:36.342
their Alpha is Elena Michaels.

09:36.344 --> 09:38.277
Is that true?

09:40.981 --> 09:43.281
I am the Alpha that you want to hunt.

09:43.283 --> 09:45.617
You have my confession,
recorded on video.

09:45.619 --> 09:49.454
And your Pack will get more than
enough satisfaction from my death.

09:50.657 --> 09:52.057
Maybe.

09:52.860 --> 09:54.260
Maybe not.

09:56.830 --> 09:58.663
_

09:58.665 --> 10:00.131
Nick, brace yourself.

10:00.132 --> 10:01.334
(GROAN)

10:01.335 --> 10:07.335
♪

10:07.674 --> 10:09.374
- (CURRENT BUZZING)
- (YELLING)

10:11.811 --> 10:13.745
(GASPS OF PAIN)

10:19.318 --> 10:21.485
You know, I'm not afraid to die,

10:21.487 --> 10:24.521
but killing an injured
man, that's a dirty play,

10:24.523 --> 10:25.990
even for you.

10:27.193 --> 10:30.227
I'm not going to kill you, Nick.

10:30.229 --> 10:31.695
Not yet.

10:31.697 --> 10:33.697
I need you to do something for me.

10:33.699 --> 10:36.233
I want Elena, here at Stonehaven.

10:36.235 --> 10:37.668
(SCOFFING)

10:37.670 --> 10:40.203
And you just assume she's
going to come here?

10:40.205 --> 10:42.673
Tell her I will kill
Jeremy if she does not.

10:42.675 --> 10:45.541
If she does not show, she's not
worthy of leading your Pack.

10:45.543 --> 10:47.443
We will hunt Jeremy.

10:47.445 --> 10:51.248
Then, we will continue the slaughter,
starting with the baby, um...

10:51.250 --> 10:53.383
Rocco, is it?

10:53.385 --> 10:55.685
I didn't know that to rise to the top,

10:55.687 --> 10:59.689
you had to stoop so low as to
threaten an innocent child.

10:59.691 --> 11:02.425
Innocent, he cannot be
innocent if he's born

11:02.427 --> 11:04.560
with original sin.

11:04.562 --> 11:08.898
Anyway, the choice is Elena's, not mine.

11:08.900 --> 11:14.900
♪

11:15.072 --> 11:17.239
She has until noon tomorrow.

11:17.241 --> 11:20.442
If she wants this to stop,
if she truly is Alpha,

11:20.444 --> 11:22.511
she will come.

11:22.513 --> 11:24.479
(DOOR OPENS, HINGES CREAK)

11:26.383 --> 11:27.783
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

11:30.454 --> 11:31.854
Elena?

11:37.761 --> 11:39.161
Elena?

11:42.933 --> 11:44.333
(SIGHING)

11:46.269 --> 11:49.103
It's not just Jeremy, he's
threatening everybody.

11:49.105 --> 11:51.940
- Including Rocco.
- Is Rachel alone?

11:51.942 --> 11:54.575
Paige is there. She's training Rachel.

11:54.577 --> 11:57.778
If I don't give myself up,
there'll just be more bloodshed.

11:57.780 --> 11:59.780
We can't trust Konstantin.

11:59.782 --> 12:01.282
We have to stick to the plan.

12:01.284 --> 12:03.284
Ambush the Russians when
they bring Jeremy out.

12:03.286 --> 12:05.119
What, just the five of us?

12:05.121 --> 12:06.921
We've called in the others.

12:08.424 --> 12:10.424
And they haven't called back, have they?

12:13.429 --> 12:16.964
He's using the War Room records
to track down the Pack.

12:16.966 --> 12:19.132
He's offering them a chance to fold in.

12:19.134 --> 12:21.268
What happens when they say "no"?

12:24.606 --> 12:27.975
- Now the Pack is dying.
- Only because they're loyal.

12:27.977 --> 12:31.444
- They chose to be so.
- We all did.

12:35.650 --> 12:38.785
Nick, go to Rachel's.

12:38.787 --> 12:42.589
If this is really it, that's
where you need to be.

12:44.993 --> 12:47.827
And if this is it?

12:47.829 --> 12:49.829
We go down swinging.

12:49.831 --> 12:55.831
♪

13:04.845 --> 13:09.916
♪

13:11.875 --> 13:14.811
(SCOFFING) Wolf surrounds himself

13:14.836 --> 13:17.370
with the artefacts of man, why?

13:17.372 --> 13:20.906
Destroyer of earth, man will
be extinct, soon enough.

13:20.908 --> 13:23.909
All these things will fade
away, burn up in smoke.

13:23.911 --> 13:26.546
All these things are mine, now.

13:26.548 --> 13:29.514
I will remove the artefacts
if they offend you.

13:30.750 --> 13:34.018
Where is your father's body?

13:34.020 --> 13:35.853
Sent back to Russia.

13:35.855 --> 13:37.855
To be laid out?

13:37.857 --> 13:39.257
To be buried.

13:40.660 --> 13:43.861
The dead still feel for a
time after their death.

13:43.863 --> 13:46.029
Your father feels your absence.

13:46.031 --> 13:47.998
How do you honour him?

13:48.000 --> 13:51.868
I will honour him by hunting the
Alpha of the North American Pack.

13:51.870 --> 13:53.870
Elena Michaels, if she shows up.

13:53.872 --> 13:57.074
- If not, Jeremy Danvers.
- The hunt honours you,

13:57.076 --> 13:58.875
not him.

13:58.877 --> 14:00.877
Danvers ripped out my father's throat.

14:00.879 --> 14:04.014
You stood by and watched, I think.

14:04.016 --> 14:07.884
Taking your father's seat
before his body hit the floor.

14:07.886 --> 14:10.053
(SCOFFING)

14:10.055 --> 14:14.057
You have always been a
little <i> mudak,</i> Konstantin.

14:14.059 --> 14:17.060
Like a puppy, showing
his white, soft belly,

14:17.062 --> 14:20.430
pissing on the rug when he is scared.

14:20.432 --> 14:26.432
♪

14:30.074 --> 14:33.243
I will kill Jeremy Danvers.

14:33.244 --> 14:34.377
What?

14:34.378 --> 14:37.246
I have an anger that needs calming.

14:37.248 --> 14:41.583
He is the one who is in the
cage, so I will take him.

14:41.585 --> 14:44.553
That was not the plan.

14:44.555 --> 14:48.457
I can be angry with him, or
I can be angry with you.

14:48.459 --> 14:49.859
You choose.

14:52.396 --> 14:55.930
And what will my men hunt?

14:55.932 --> 14:58.066
Their convictions.

14:59.770 --> 15:01.770
I see it now.

15:01.772 --> 15:03.938
This is a wolf.

15:03.940 --> 15:06.908
Finally, something good in this house.

15:08.245 --> 15:10.544
CLAY: Okay now, you do the same.

15:10.546 --> 15:11.980
Pull your arm back.

15:12.883 --> 15:14.283
(IMPACT OF KNIFE ON TARGET)

15:14.284 --> 15:15.817
ALEXEI: Straight to the throat.

15:15.819 --> 15:19.988
♪

15:19.990 --> 15:22.257
CLAY: And you throw it right through.

15:22.259 --> 15:24.492
Keep your eye on the target.

15:24.494 --> 15:26.794
I see your concern.

15:26.796 --> 15:28.429
(SIGHING)

15:28.431 --> 15:32.132
Four of us against the Russians.

15:32.134 --> 15:35.303
Twelve hours before
all our lives change.

15:35.305 --> 15:37.971
For the good, or the bad.

15:37.973 --> 15:40.107
Or they don't change at all.

15:42.511 --> 15:43.911
That's worse.

15:50.986 --> 15:53.153
Your mother would do this, too.

15:53.155 --> 15:57.123
She would go quiet when she
was working out the plan.

15:59.160 --> 16:00.993
The less anyone knows, the better.

16:00.995 --> 16:02.462
I thought that once, too.

16:02.464 --> 16:05.298
But then I found you, and you helped me.

16:07.001 --> 16:08.968
Let me do the same for you.

16:13.007 --> 16:15.174
I keep seeing this premonition,

16:15.176 --> 16:17.810
of me, burning the house to the ground.

16:17.812 --> 16:21.680
Paige said it won't
stop until it happens.

16:21.682 --> 16:25.184
Until... what happens?

16:25.186 --> 16:27.820
Until I burn it down.

16:27.822 --> 16:31.857
There has to be something more
than just an eye for an eye.

16:31.859 --> 16:33.492
This has to end.

16:34.862 --> 16:36.862
Elena?

16:36.864 --> 16:38.497
Promise me you won't stop me.

16:40.167 --> 16:43.201
And promise me that you won't
tell Clay, not until it's over.

16:43.203 --> 16:45.337
He can't know what I'm going to do.

16:46.206 --> 16:49.040
But when it's done...

16:49.042 --> 16:51.176
I want him to know why.

16:58.051 --> 17:00.051
- Where's Paige?
- Gone.

17:00.053 --> 17:02.220
- Where?
- Elena called 10 minutes ago.

17:02.222 --> 17:04.054
She had something for her to do.

17:04.056 --> 17:06.891
No, no, she's got to get back here.

17:06.893 --> 17:08.526
- She said it was urgent.
- Okay.

17:08.528 --> 17:10.171
Pack your things. We got
to get out of here.

17:10.195 --> 17:14.231
- Let's go, now.
- A "hello" would be nice.

17:14.233 --> 17:17.702
Rachel, the Russians
are on their way here.

17:17.704 --> 17:20.704
I'm not running. Rocco's
been through enough.

17:20.705 --> 17:23.040
- And you're obviously injured.
- No, we have to go.

17:23.041 --> 17:27.077
Look, I'm not exactly in the
best fighting form here.

17:28.079 --> 17:29.480
I am.

17:29.481 --> 17:35.481
♪

17:38.957 --> 17:41.391
(EERIE WHISPERS)

17:46.264 --> 17:48.932
Bones can't be that
much different, right?

17:48.934 --> 17:54.934
♪

18:03.949 --> 18:09.949
♪

18:20.965 --> 18:23.098
Tomorrow, we attack our home.

18:29.673 --> 18:31.340
This...

18:31.342 --> 18:32.742
is home.

18:33.677 --> 18:39.677
♪

18:48.692 --> 18:54.692
♪

18:59.335 --> 19:01.135
I'm not broken.

19:03.506 --> 19:04.906
I know.

19:04.907 --> 19:10.907
♪

19:19.922 --> 19:25.922
♪

19:36.078 --> 19:37.478
ALEXEI: Elena?

19:46.255 --> 19:48.088
Our truck, he took it!

19:49.608 --> 19:51.008
My dad's gone.

19:51.894 --> 19:55.396
After everything we've been
through, he just left.

19:57.266 --> 19:59.266
I know this doesn't make
any sense right now,

19:59.268 --> 20:02.569
but you need to know that
our father is a good man.

20:02.571 --> 20:05.405
Everything he's ever done
has been to protect you.

20:06.475 --> 20:10.109
To protect us.

20:10.111 --> 20:11.511
Well now there's three of us.

20:13.649 --> 20:15.181
We stick to the plan.

20:15.183 --> 20:17.050
In four hours, they'll bring Jeremy out.

20:17.052 --> 20:19.118
We hide in the woods, and we rescue him.

20:19.120 --> 20:20.954
You're my Alpha.

20:20.956 --> 20:22.356
What you ask, I do.

20:24.792 --> 20:26.492
And weapons?

20:26.494 --> 20:27.894
Just knives.

20:29.664 --> 20:31.064
I'm good with that.

20:36.938 --> 20:40.606
You jumped to Sasha's defence
pretty quickly after he ran away.

20:41.976 --> 20:43.442
Unless he didn't.

20:44.679 --> 20:46.079
Do you trust me?

20:47.314 --> 20:48.714
Lil' bit, darlin'.

20:48.716 --> 20:54.716
♪

21:03.730 --> 21:09.730
♪

21:18.745 --> 21:24.315
♪

21:29.655 --> 21:33.024
Is it part of some kind
of spell, or something?

21:33.026 --> 21:34.426
Squeeze.

21:37.830 --> 21:41.031
Hit him in the eyes, and
abracadabra, he's blind.

21:41.033 --> 21:44.001
Then punch him in the face.

21:44.003 --> 21:48.371
This is a long way from prepping
brunches in Toronto, huh?

21:48.373 --> 21:51.207
Can't go back to that,
even if I wanted to.

21:51.209 --> 21:53.043
I belong to a Coven now.

21:53.045 --> 21:55.378
So I get to make my own decisions.

21:55.380 --> 21:58.214
Where I live, how I live.

21:58.216 --> 22:00.383
I'm not a threat anymore.

22:00.385 --> 22:03.553
I actually own a stake
in the secrecy, too.

22:03.555 --> 22:07.357
And... you don't have
to take care of us.

22:10.228 --> 22:11.628
Rachel.

22:15.033 --> 22:17.900
When I said there's no
place else I'd rather be,

22:17.902 --> 22:19.569
I meant that.

22:19.571 --> 22:22.404
It's just... look, I feel...

22:22.406 --> 22:25.708
Nick, let's get through today.

22:27.244 --> 22:31.380
We have all of our
tomorrows to figure...

22:33.084 --> 22:34.716
To figure this out.

22:38.255 --> 22:40.389
(INHALING) 'Kay.

22:41.658 --> 22:47.658
♪

22:56.473 --> 22:57.873
(EXHALING)

22:57.874 --> 23:03.874
♪

23:12.888 --> 23:18.888
♪

23:22.765 --> 23:24.165
(CLOSING DRAWER)

23:24.166 --> 23:30.166
♪

23:39.181 --> 23:45.181
♪

23:53.995 --> 23:56.295
(GURGLING)

24:09.177 --> 24:15.177
♪

24:19.887 --> 24:22.588
(GASPING)

24:22.590 --> 24:23.990
(CHOKING)

24:26.526 --> 24:28.560
(VERTEBRAE CRACKING)

24:28.562 --> 24:31.029
I didn't kill him right.
I'm so sorry, Elena.

24:31.031 --> 24:33.699
- I need you to go with Clay.
- What about the plan?

24:33.701 --> 24:36.367
This is the plan. Go with Clay.

24:36.369 --> 24:38.369
Save Jeremy.

24:38.371 --> 24:41.039
This isn't up for discussion.

24:41.041 --> 24:43.508
- Go.
- (VERTEBRAE CRACKING)

24:45.044 --> 24:46.444
Where's Elena?

24:48.915 --> 24:50.315
She sent me here.

24:53.953 --> 24:57.955
(DISTANT WHISTLING)

25:00.559 --> 25:02.659
(WHISPERING) Shh, shh, let's go.

25:02.660 --> 25:03.929
Come on.

25:03.930 --> 25:08.398
(WHISTLING CONTINUES)

25:08.400 --> 25:09.934
It can't be.

25:09.936 --> 25:12.069
CLAY: I killed him.

25:12.071 --> 25:14.404
How is he still alive?

25:14.406 --> 25:16.240
What do we do?

25:16.242 --> 25:18.041
We save Jeremy.

25:18.043 --> 25:21.378
_

25:30.387 --> 25:32.535
_

25:36.645 --> 25:38.403
_

25:40.399 --> 25:41.799
_

25:41.800 --> 25:43.200
(DOOR OPENING)

25:46.271 --> 25:47.671
(DOOR CLOSING)

25:49.807 --> 25:51.207
I'm here.

25:52.443 --> 25:54.176
As requested.

25:54.178 --> 25:59.515
♪

26:03.797 --> 26:05.763
I am the Alpha that you want.

26:07.068 --> 26:08.468
Release Jeremy.

26:08.469 --> 26:10.102
That part is out of my hands now.

26:10.104 --> 26:12.637
- The Albino has him.
- The Albino is dead.

26:12.639 --> 26:14.105
The one who keeps lists, yes.

26:14.107 --> 26:17.007
The one who has Jeremy is not so...

26:17.009 --> 26:18.409
reasonable.

26:19.111 --> 26:20.511
Twins.

26:20.512 --> 26:22.646
Yes, they used it to their advantage.

26:22.648 --> 26:24.648
Two wolves with the same scent.

26:24.650 --> 26:26.984
Always one step ahead of you.

26:26.986 --> 26:29.653
Always able to be in two places at once.

26:29.655 --> 26:31.221
Never afraid to die

26:31.223 --> 26:33.990
because the other one was
always there to finish the job.

26:33.992 --> 26:36.826
And what will you do once
the surviving one is dead?

26:36.828 --> 26:38.828
There'll be no one left
to finish the job,

26:38.829 --> 26:40.131
Jeremy will be free.

26:40.132 --> 26:42.499
You have a lot of faith
in your former Alpha.

26:42.501 --> 26:44.834
I have a lot of faith in my Pack.

26:44.836 --> 26:46.669
What remains of it.

26:46.671 --> 26:50.339
How many are left? Two,
maybe three others?

26:50.341 --> 26:52.508
I've killed them all.

26:52.510 --> 26:54.209
It is over, Elena.

26:54.211 --> 27:00.211
♪

27:06.857 --> 27:10.225
(FIGHTING GRUNTS)

27:10.227 --> 27:11.627
- (THUD)
- Argh!

27:13.131 --> 27:14.531
(GASPING)

27:14.532 --> 27:17.299
(GRUNTS)

27:17.301 --> 27:19.401
(EERIE WHISPERS)

27:19.403 --> 27:25.373
♪

27:25.375 --> 27:27.075
Aargh... ah!

27:27.077 --> 27:31.880
♪

27:31.882 --> 27:33.282
(VERTEBRAE CRACKING)

27:38.388 --> 27:42.190
♪

27:42.192 --> 27:45.326
Do you believe in tradition
of good death, bad death?

27:48.064 --> 27:50.364
The only good death is old age.

27:51.901 --> 27:54.735
And there are no good
deaths in our world.

27:54.737 --> 27:57.738
But there can be glorious death.

27:57.740 --> 28:00.207
That is what I will give to you.

28:01.577 --> 28:04.078
And after it is over,

28:04.080 --> 28:07.748
I will collect the rocks for your grave.

28:07.750 --> 28:09.150
There won't be many.

28:10.285 --> 28:12.419
I may...

28:12.421 --> 28:14.153
eat some of you.

28:14.155 --> 28:16.189
(CHUCKLING)

28:17.759 --> 28:19.159
(DISTANT RUSTLING)

28:20.429 --> 28:22.429
(SNIFFING)

28:22.431 --> 28:24.897
Come out, little pup!

28:26.301 --> 28:28.067
Alexei Antonov!

28:32.440 --> 28:35.374
You smell of fear.

28:41.449 --> 28:47.449
♪

28:50.625 --> 28:52.458
(IMPACT THUDS)

28:52.459 --> 28:53.793
- (STABBING IMPACT)
- (THUD)

28:53.794 --> 28:59.164
♪

28:59.165 --> 29:00.533
(SCREAMING)

29:00.534 --> 29:01.735
CLAY: Jeremy!

29:01.736 --> 29:03.136
(ATTACK YELL)

29:04.138 --> 29:06.404
- Go, get him out of here!
- I got him!

29:06.406 --> 29:12.406
♪

29:17.050 --> 29:23.050
♪

29:33.366 --> 29:37.501
(CHOKING)

29:37.503 --> 29:40.004
Little Antonov.

29:40.006 --> 29:42.807
It wasn't just your sister
that I killed, was it?

29:44.010 --> 29:47.678
Your mother's blood
tasted of crushed hope.

29:47.680 --> 29:53.680
♪

29:53.686 --> 29:55.452
(CHOKING)

29:55.454 --> 29:58.689
♪

29:58.691 --> 30:00.091
(KNIFE IMPACT)

30:01.193 --> 30:02.593
(SIGH)

30:03.796 --> 30:05.196
(PANTING)

30:06.231 --> 30:09.598
(SINGING WEAKLY IN RUSSIAN)

30:09.600 --> 30:15.600
♪

30:17.242 --> 30:18.642
Jeremy.

30:20.611 --> 30:22.345
Where's Elena?

30:22.347 --> 30:25.047
KONSTANTIN: I'm trying
to offer you a way out,

30:25.049 --> 30:27.416
end this brutality with us.

30:27.418 --> 30:30.052
We are family, Elena.

30:30.054 --> 30:33.021
You want one Pack, under one Alpha.

30:34.225 --> 30:36.225
I'm never going to let that happen.

30:36.227 --> 30:39.895
I have all the cards.
Can you not see this?

30:39.897 --> 30:41.297
Change is coming.

30:42.900 --> 30:45.033
But it can be good for all of us.

30:49.439 --> 30:51.073
(MIXED CHATTER)

30:51.075 --> 30:52.475
PAIGE: Ready?

30:58.248 --> 31:01.115
This is everything that
Alexei needs to know.

31:08.291 --> 31:14.291
♪

31:18.301 --> 31:20.368
<i>Dorme.</i>

31:20.370 --> 31:21.770
(IMPACT THUD)

31:24.874 --> 31:27.574
WOMAN: Good afternoon, and
thank you for coming today.

31:27.576 --> 31:30.378
Mayor Sam Talbot will
be arriving shortly.

31:31.614 --> 31:33.014
Give me my phone,

31:33.015 --> 31:34.215
let me tell them that you're on side

31:34.216 --> 31:36.116
before it's too late.

31:36.118 --> 31:38.118
I will lead you and your Pack

31:38.120 --> 31:40.421
through what's to come.

31:40.423 --> 31:44.625
You want to lead <i> me</i>
through what is to come?

31:44.626 --> 31:45.827
(IMPACT)

31:45.828 --> 31:48.628
I will lead you...

31:48.630 --> 31:50.030
to your death.

31:52.109 --> 31:54.158
WOMAN: The mayor will
make a brief statement,

31:54.219 --> 31:57.454
and then we'll open the floor
to address your questions.

31:58.339 --> 32:01.006
ELENA'S VOICE: <i>We've both
loved and lost in this world,</i>

32:01.031 --> 32:03.164
because of this world.

32:03.166 --> 32:06.334
There was never room for
love, never room for trust.

32:06.336 --> 32:08.536
Without those, what's the point?

32:08.538 --> 32:10.371
But...

32:10.373 --> 32:11.773
How?

32:14.242 --> 32:16.242
How do we change?

32:16.244 --> 32:18.077
We can't hide anymore.

32:18.079 --> 32:19.712
We have to tell the truth.

32:19.714 --> 32:21.848
That's all I've ever wanted.

32:21.850 --> 32:27.850
♪

32:31.058 --> 32:34.727
MAYOR TALBOT: It's with a heavy
heart I stand before you today

32:34.729 --> 32:38.597
to speak on your concerns
about safety in our town.

32:38.599 --> 32:41.267
So we've hired more officers.

32:41.269 --> 32:43.935
We've set up a special hotline.

32:43.937 --> 32:45.737
I wanted to make this work.

32:47.274 --> 32:49.274
I wanted to save you.

32:49.276 --> 32:51.810
There is no saving us.

32:51.812 --> 32:53.645
Not if we stay the same.

32:53.647 --> 32:56.948
MAYOR TALBOT: Most of
you knew Karen Morgan.

32:56.950 --> 32:58.583
She came from Baltimore,

32:58.585 --> 33:02.953
and she had hopes of
settling into our community.

33:02.955 --> 33:04.621
These heinous crimes

33:04.623 --> 33:07.457
are being thoroughly investigated

33:07.459 --> 33:09.826
at the county and state level.

33:09.828 --> 33:11.828
(DEEP SIGH)

33:11.830 --> 33:13.764
And I can assure you

33:13.766 --> 33:16.466
that we at Bear Valley City Hall

33:16.468 --> 33:18.669
will be there to...

33:18.671 --> 33:20.837
(MIXED WHISPERS)

33:20.839 --> 33:22.738
...hear your concerns.

33:22.740 --> 33:26.776
♪

33:26.777 --> 33:27.978
May I help you, bud?

33:27.979 --> 33:30.513
You are the ones who can help.

33:30.515 --> 33:32.916
It's time for you to know our truth.

33:32.917 --> 33:34.251
(INQUISITIVE CHATTER)

33:34.252 --> 33:37.920
There are those of us who are different.

33:40.858 --> 33:42.792
But understand...

33:44.495 --> 33:46.329
we are all the same.

33:46.331 --> 33:49.264
We... we all have hope...

33:50.335 --> 33:52.301
for better tomorrow.

33:56.173 --> 33:57.940
- (BONES CRACKING)
- (MOANING)

33:59.376 --> 34:01.076
(SHOCKED REACTIONS)

34:01.078 --> 34:02.544
MAN: What's his problem?

34:02.546 --> 34:04.679
(STRUGGLING MOANS)

34:04.681 --> 34:07.883
- (GROANING)
- (GASPS, YELPS)

34:09.485 --> 34:10.886
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

34:10.887 --> 34:16.887
♪

34:18.829 --> 34:20.795
(LOW GROWL)

34:25.534 --> 34:28.202
Take her out. Kill her.

34:28.204 --> 34:30.036
However you wish.

34:30.039 --> 34:32.505
She's my gift to you.

34:35.543 --> 34:37.844
(CELLPHONE BUZZING)

34:39.148 --> 34:40.547
You're going to want to check that.

34:40.549 --> 34:42.216
KONSTANTIN: Text from Clay?

34:42.217 --> 34:45.018
I have a heart, but this
will not change anything.

34:45.020 --> 34:48.722
That sound is the end of our story.

34:48.724 --> 34:50.290
And the beginning of another.

34:50.292 --> 34:51.759
Nonsense.

34:51.761 --> 34:54.561
That sound means the world
now knows what we are.

34:54.563 --> 34:57.197
I offered you a way out.

34:57.199 --> 35:01.067
But I knew you'd refuse, you
would try to wipe out my Pack.

35:01.069 --> 35:02.568
My family.

35:02.570 --> 35:04.237
And nothing would ever change.

35:04.239 --> 35:06.539
Not unless we changed everything.

35:10.745 --> 35:13.046
The secret was killing us.

35:13.048 --> 35:15.782
And we were killing them for knowing.

35:15.784 --> 35:18.284
(GROWLING)

35:18.286 --> 35:20.853
(MIXED MURMURS)

35:23.425 --> 35:25.958
(CAMERA FLASHES SNAPPING)

35:27.762 --> 35:30.630
Too many innocent people have died.

35:30.632 --> 35:32.799
For us.

35:32.801 --> 35:34.201
No more.

35:38.272 --> 35:39.905
Do you realize what you have done?

35:41.608 --> 35:45.244
Everything we do, we now
do under human law.

35:45.246 --> 35:49.281
If you want to kill me, you will be
caught and convicted as a human.

35:49.283 --> 35:51.450
You will do your time.

35:51.452 --> 35:55.286
You'll be forced to
Change in a prison cell.

35:55.288 --> 35:56.688
It's your call.

35:59.626 --> 36:02.627
You are naive enough to believe
that they will accept us?

36:02.629 --> 36:04.663
There will be those who won't.

36:06.166 --> 36:08.632
(CONTINUED LOW GROWLS)

36:11.204 --> 36:13.737
(CONCERNED MURMURS)

36:13.739 --> 36:18.809
♪

36:18.811 --> 36:21.079
WOMAN: Oh, no, no, no... Stay back!

36:23.483 --> 36:24.883
(WHIMPER)

36:24.884 --> 36:26.084
No!

36:26.085 --> 36:27.485
No!

36:29.121 --> 36:31.689
KONSTANTIN: You destroyed everything.

36:31.691 --> 36:33.091
No.

36:34.326 --> 36:36.961
I've destroyed Packs.

36:36.963 --> 36:40.163
I've destroyed the way that we organize.

36:40.165 --> 36:42.332
No more Alphas,

36:42.334 --> 36:43.734
including you.

36:45.771 --> 36:47.171
What now?

36:47.172 --> 36:48.572
I'm going to live my life.

36:50.509 --> 36:52.476
You should secure your assets.

36:54.846 --> 36:56.980
If I don't walk out of this house alive,

36:56.982 --> 36:58.681
a list of Russian Pack
names will be released

36:58.683 --> 37:03.185
to the authorities in Moscow.

37:03.187 --> 37:05.655
Go home, uncle.

37:10.361 --> 37:11.761
_

37:12.597 --> 37:13.997
_

37:13.998 --> 37:17.533
ELENA'S VOICE: I know at first
their reaction will be fear

37:17.535 --> 37:20.836
And I know that if I Change,
with these wounds...

37:22.373 --> 37:26.008
I'll die anyway.

37:26.010 --> 37:28.677
But it's a sacrifice that
I'm willing to make.

37:31.916 --> 37:33.316
Let me do this.

37:34.384 --> 37:36.384
Let me do this so you can live.

37:36.386 --> 37:39.120
Over time, no, there will be tolerance.

37:40.390 --> 37:41.890
There has to be.

37:41.892 --> 37:46.561
And if this means a better
life for you and Alexei...

37:46.563 --> 37:49.697
Please, let me be the one to go.

37:52.102 --> 37:54.035
I am so sorry.

37:56.573 --> 37:58.706
Call an ambulance.

38:01.411 --> 38:03.044
You're going to be okay now.

38:03.046 --> 38:05.580
No one else is going to hurt you.

38:05.582 --> 38:07.181
I got you now.

38:09.218 --> 38:12.219
They will know that you
did this for them.

38:12.221 --> 38:15.322
And they will be so proud
to call you father.

38:15.324 --> 38:20.260
♪

38:20.261 --> 38:21.529
(MOANING)

38:21.530 --> 38:27.530
♪

38:32.174 --> 38:38.174
♪

38:47.188 --> 38:53.159
♪

38:53.161 --> 38:55.794
To be sure of your safety,

38:55.796 --> 38:57.930
the safety of the Pack...

38:58.799 --> 39:00.933
You need to burn the names.

39:02.003 --> 39:03.969
Elena.

39:03.971 --> 39:06.772
You're going to take
the whole thing down.

39:09.476 --> 39:12.544
(LIQUID SPLASHING)

39:12.546 --> 39:18.546
♪

39:21.656 --> 39:23.122
(CANISTER CLATTERING)

39:23.124 --> 39:29.124
♪

39:38.138 --> 39:44.138
♪

39:44.210 --> 39:45.610
You do it.

39:46.377 --> 39:47.777
No.

39:47.778 --> 39:50.278
This is your house to burn.

39:50.280 --> 39:56.280
♪

40:05.295 --> 40:11.295
♪

40:20.309 --> 40:26.309
♪

40:35.057 --> 40:37.524
(FLAMES ROARING)

40:39.316 --> 40:40.716
And then what?

40:42.331 --> 40:45.032
You thought about what happens next?

40:45.034 --> 40:51.034
♪

41:00.048 --> 41:06.048
♪

41:12.932 --> 41:15.365
RADIO HOST: <i>And in local
news, here in Bear Valley</i>

41:15.390 --> 41:18.659
<i>an anonymous tip in the
disappearance of Karen Morgan</i>

41:18.661 --> 41:20.760
<i>may lead to a resolution in the case.</i>

41:20.762 --> 41:22.162
(MIXED SHOUTS)

41:22.164 --> 41:24.397
RADIO HOST 2: <i>The Komi
Republic has reported</i>

41:24.399 --> 41:27.500
<i>a significantly higher
population of wolves this year.</i>

41:27.502 --> 41:29.835
<i>The government has reinstated a bounty</i>

41:29.837 --> 41:31.538
<i>set at 100,000 Rubles.</i>

41:31.540 --> 41:33.739
RADIO HOST 3: <i>News of a one-legged
werewolf found in Texas,</i>

41:33.741 --> 41:35.941
<i>having crossed the
border in wolf form...</i>

41:35.943 --> 41:37.710
RADIO HOST 4: <i>...in
Winnipeg have claimed</i>

41:37.712 --> 41:40.546
<i>as many as five werewolves
have been given sanctuary...</i>

41:40.547 --> 41:46.547
♪

41:54.568 --> 41:56.401
ELENA'S VOICE: <i>We'll live our lives.</i>

41:57.995 --> 42:01.662
We finally get to choose
our own destinies.

42:01.868 --> 42:07.868
♪

42:16.883 --> 42:22.883
♪

42:26.792 --> 42:32.792
♪

42:41.807 --> 42:47.756
♪

42:47.857 --> 42:49.724
What now, darlin'?

42:49.782 --> 42:53.803
♪

42:53.832 --> 42:55.832
We go.

